38
00:02:04,909 --> 00:02:06,340
are.

39
00:02:06,340 --> 00:02:09,979
Some people like new experiences, others not so much.

40
00:02:09,979 --> 00:02:12,069
Some people are more reliable than others.

41
00:02:12,069 --> 00:02:15,809
Some people are more outgoing when they’re in a new environment, others might be more

42
00:02:15,809 --> 00:02:18,540
shy when meeting new people.

43
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:20,299
People deal with stress differently.

44
00:02:20,299 --> 00:02:24,340
In stressful situations, some people seem to have more control over their emotions than

45
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:26,110
others.

46
00:02:26,110 --> 00:02:30,439
Personality refers to a particular pattern of behaviour and thinking that prevails across

47
00:02:30,439 --> 00:02:34,870
time and situations, and makes us different from other people.

48
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:39,949
Here, the goal is to discover the CAUSES of individual differences in behaviour from a

49
00:02:39,949 --> 00:02:41,879
PERSONALITY perspective.

50
00:02:41,879 --> 00:02:47,579
Whereas in Social Psychology, the focus is on the social influences on behaviour.

51
00:02:47,579 --> 00:02:51,299
Understanding personality, and measuring it, is important in many areas in psychology,

52
00:02:51,299 --> 00:02:54,040
and especially so in clinical psychology.

53
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:59,189
So, what researchers try to do is identify personality characteristics, figure out what

54
00:02:59,189 --> 00:03:02,730
variables produce and control those characteristics.

55
00:03:02,730 --> 00:03:05,559
To do this, they take a couple of different approaches.

56
00:03:05,559 --> 00:03:09,489
The one we&#39;re going to focus on is the nomothetic approach.

57
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:13,790
This approach involves trying to understand personality by identifying GENERAL rules that

58
00:03:13,790 --> 00:03:16,680
govern the behaviour of ALL individuals.

59
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:21,419
The idiographic approach is used when people are interested in understanding personality

60
00:03:21,419 --> 00:03:25,650
by identifying the UNIQUE configuration of characteristics and life history within the

61
00:03:25,650 --> 00:03:27,120
INDIVIDUAL person.

62
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:31,769
We will be talking about the GENERAL rules that relate to personality, which is the nomothetic

63
00:03:31,769 --> 00:03:32,269
approach.

